			<div id="main">
				<h1 class="title">A universal proof checker</h1>
				<h2> What is Dedukti? </h2>
				<p>
				Dedukti is a universal proof checker, based on the λΠ-calculus modulo.<br />
				The project is named after the word for "to deduce" in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esperanto">Esperanto</a>.<br />
				</p>

				<h2>How to get/install/use Dedukti?</h2>
                                <p>
				  <a href="manual.html">See the manual.</a>
                                </p>
                                <p>
				  There is also a <a href="tutorial.html">tutorial</a>.
                                </p>

				<h2>Publications</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Ronan Saillard, Towards explicit rewrite rules in the lambda-Pi calculus modulo. <a href="http://hal.inria.fr/docs/00/92/99/12/PDF/article.pdf">PDF</a></li>
					<li>Ali Assaf, Raphaël Cauderlier and Ronan Saillard, Dedukti un vérificateur de preuves universel. <a href="poster.pdf">POSTER</a></li>
					<li>Mathieu Boespflug, Quentin Carbonneaux and Olivier Hermant, The lambda-Pi-calculus Modulo as a Universal Proof Language. In PxTP 2012.  <a href="http://ceur-ws.org/Vol-878/paper2.pdf">PDF</a></li>
					<li>Mathieu Boespflug and Guillaume Burel, CoqInE: Translating the Calculus of Inductive Constructions into the lambda-Pi-calculus Modulo. In PxTP 2012.<a href="http://ceur-ws.org/Vol-878/paper3.pdf">PDF</a></li>
				</ul>

                                <h2>Translators to Dedukti</h2>
                                <ul>
					<li><a href = "http://www.ensiie.fr/~guillaume.burel/blackandwhite_coqInE.html.en">CoqInE</a> (Coq In dEdukti) produces Dedukti proofs from Coq proofs.</li>
					<li><a href = "https://www.rocq.inria.fr/deducteam/Holide/index.html">Holide</a> (HOL In DEdukti) produces Dedukti proofs from HOL proofs, using the <a href = "http://www.gilith.com/research/opentheory/">Open Theory</a> standard. </li>
					<li><a href = "https://www.rocq.inria.fr/deducteam/Focalide/index.html">Focalide</a> (FoCaLize In DEdukti) produces Dedukti files from FoCaLize developments.</li>
                                </ul>
				<h2>Dedukti developments</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><a href = "https://www.rocq.inria.fr/deducteam/Sigmaid/index.html">Sigmaid</a> (SIGMA-calculus In Dedukti) is an encoding of the simply-typed &sigmaf;-calculus in Dedukti.</li>
					<li><a href = "https://github.com/rafoo/dklib">Dklib</a> is a library defining basic data structures.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
